Ingredients
* 1 pound carrots, thinner is better
* 2 Tablespoons butter +
* 1 pound (box) brown sugar
* 1 cup water
* salt
* pepper

Directions
* Wash carrots
* melt butter in large saucepan
* combine carrots and water and brown sugar in saucepan
* salt and pepper to taste
* bring to boil over high, stir/flip carrots frequently
* reduce to simmer (medium low) for 20 minutes + until carrots are tender, , stir/flip carrots frequently

You end up with a carrot caramel leftover, i want to try cooling on wax paper....

Notes
Taken from https://www.thespruceeats.com/brown-sugar-glazed-carrots-3052478
